<TITLE> DMP revives special drive Friday night </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka city police chief has said they will launch a 'special' anticrime drive at midnight Friday. "We will revive the drive that ended a few days ago to prevent mugging, robbery as it brought great results," said Naim Ahmed while speaking at 34th anniversary of Dhaka Metropolitan Police. Police would also check vehicles putting road blocks in the city, he said. Six more police stations in addition to 35 would be set up to deliver improved services, he said. He asked the car owners to keep their drivers' biodata to prevent car theft. Home minister Sahara Khatun was present at the opening ceremony as chief guest. Among others present were inspector general of police Noor Mohammad, director general of Rapid Action Battalion Hasan Mahmud Khandaker and senior police officers were present.
